1. e4 {Marin} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bb3 b5 8. Bg5 Be7 9. Qf3 Qb6 10. O-O-O Nbd7 11. Rhe1 h6 (11... O-O 12. Qg3 $14 Nc5 $6 13. Bh6 Ne8 14. Nf5 (14. f4 Kh8 $36 {Alozy,F-Odebrecht,A/corr 1995/Corr 2004 (1/2, 37)} 15. Bg5) 14... exf5 (14... Nxb3+ $14 15. axb3 exf5 16. exf5 d5 17. Bxg7 Nxg7 18. Rxe7 Bxf5 19. Nxd5 Qh6+ 20. Kb1 Rfd8) 15. exf5 $2 Qd8 16. Rxe7 Qxe7 17. Nd5 Qd8 18. Re1 Ne6 19. fxe6 fxe6 $132 {Whitlock,H-Dive,R/NZL-ch63 corr 1996/Corr 2000 (1/2, 48)} 20. Bg5 Qa5 21. Bd2 (21. Ne7+ Kh8 22. Re3) 21... Qd8 $14 22. Bg5 $5 Qa5 23. Bd2 Qd8 24. Bg5) (11... Nc5 12. Nf5 exf5 13. Bxf6 gxf6 14. Nd5 Qd8 15. exf5 Ra7 16. Qg4 $1 $11 {[%cal Gb7b6]} Kf8 $2 17. Re3 $1 $17 h5 18. Qf4 $1 {[%cal Gh4b4]} a5 19. a3 $1 $11 Nxb3+ $5 $14 20. cxb3 {, as in the line with 20.d2, is less effective here, because of} Rc7+ {We can notice the difference. The d4-pawn is over proyected now and White can create the threat of xf5 at a convenient moment, thus releasing the pressure against d4 and discouraging ...e5.} 21. Kb1 Kg7 $14 22. Rg3+ Kf8 23. Re3 Kg7 24. Rde1 Bf8 25. Rg3+ Kh7 26. Re8) 12. e5 Bb7 13. Qh3 dxe5 (13... Nxe5 14. Bxe6 fxe6 15. Qxe6 $16 {Messing,H (2355)-Begovac,F (2405)/Pula 1993/EXT 99 (1-0, 31)} Qd8 16. Bxf6 $1 $132 {Badii,M (2255)-Fillon,D/Paris 1994/EXT 98 (1-0, 36)} gxf6 17. f4 Bc8 18. Qd5 Bg4 19. fxe5 dxe5 20. Qc6+ Bd7 21. Qf3 Qb8 (21... exd4 22. Nd5 Bc6 23. Qh5+ Kf8 24. Nf4 Qd6 25. Ne6+) 22. Nd5 Rf8 $13 {Deschner,J-Joost,S/GER-ch qgA36 corr9395 1993/Corr Nr. 1 (1-0, 36)} 23. Nc7+ Qxc7 24. Qxa8+) 14. Nxe6 fxe6 15. Bxe6 Rd8 (15... Nf8 16. Rxe5 Nxe6 17. Rxe6 Qc5 18. Be3 (18. Bxf6 gxf6 19. Rde1 Rh7 20. Kb1 Kf8 21. Qg3 Rg7 22. Qxg7+ $14 Kxg7 23. Rxe7+ Kh8 24. Rxb7 Qxf2 25. Rbe7) 18... Qc8 (18... Qc7 19. Bb6 Qf4+ 20. Be3 Qc7) 19. Bd4 Kf7 20. Rde1 Re8 (20... Bd8 21. Qf5 Bc6 22. Bxf6 Bxf6 23. Ne4 Bxe4 24. R1xe4 Qd8 25. Qh5+ Kf8 26. Qc5+ Kf7 27. Qh5+ g6 $1 $18) 21. Qf5 Bxg2 22. Bxf6 Bxf6 23. Rxf6+ gxf6 24. Qh7+ Kf8 25. Qh8+) (15... Nc5 16. Bxf6 Nxe6 17. Qh5+ Kf8 18. Bxe7+ $16 Kxe7 $2 19. Qxe5 $17 Rhg8 20. f4 g6 21. g4) 16. Rxd7 Rxd7 17. Bxf6 Rd6 18. Qh5+ Kd8 19. Bxe7+ Kxe7 20. Qxe5 Kd8 {This move strengthens White's centre, but it is not easy to find a way to obtain effective counterplay.} 21. Nd5 (21. Bd5 Rf6 (21... Bxd5 22. Nxd5 Qc5 23. Qxg7 Rxd5 24. Qxh8+) 22. Qe7+ Kc8 23. Qxg7 Rhf8 24. Re7 Bc6 25. Ne4 Bxd5 26. Nxf6 Qxf6 27. Re8+) 21... Bxd5 22. Bxd5 Qc7 23. f4 Rd7 24. Qf5 (24. g3 Qxe5 25. Rxe5) 24... Qc5 25. Be6 (25. Rd1 Re8 26. g3 Qe3+ 27. Kb1 Qf2 (27... Qd2 28. Qxd7+ Kxd7 29. Be6+ Kxe6 30. Rxd2)) 25... Qf2 $5 {An interesting, but insufficient sacrifice, offering only some practical chances in a difficult position.} (25... Qf2 26. Rh1 (26. Rd1 Qe3+ 27. Kb1 Rxd1#) 26... Qd2+ 27. Kb1 Qd1+ 28. Rxd1 Rxd1#) 1/2-1/2


