1. d4 {Kostakiev,D Kostakiev,D Kostakiev,D Kostakiev,D: 'Kostakiev,Dimitar Kostakiev,Dimitar: 'Kostakiev,D''} Nf6 2. Bg5 c5 3. Bxf6 gxf6 4. d5 Qb6 5. Qc1 f5 6. g3 d6 (6... Bg7 7. c3 d6 8. Nd2 O-O 9. Nh3 Nd7 10. Nc4 Qa6 11. Qf4 Nf6) 7. Bg2 $5 {Bohatirchuk 1934. Long years Botvinnik and Fischer kept different opposit oppinions about the line starting with 3...b4. Finaly In tom 3 of his splendid last books Botvinik recgnized that 7.g4! is giving advantage to White. Statistic confirmed - 56%:44%. Besides it two other variations draws attention:} Nd7 8. Nh3 (8. Nd2) 8... Nf6 (8... Bg7 9. c3 Nf6 10. Nd2 Qa6 11. Qc2 e5) 9. Nd2 Bg7 10. O-O O-O (10... e6 11. Nc4 Qa6 12. Ne3 O-O 13. c4) 11. Rd1 Bd7 (11... e5 12. dxe6 Bxe6 13. Nf4 d5 14. c4 Rfd8 (14... Ne4 15. cxd5 Bxb2 16. Qc2 Bxa1 17. Nxe4 fxe4 18. dxe6 Bg7 19. Bxe4) 15. Qc2) 12. c3 Qa6 13. Qc2 Rae8 (13... Qxe2 14. Re1 Qa6 15. Rxe7 Rfe8 16. Rxd7 Nxd7 17. Qxf5 Nf6 18. Ne4) 14. e4 $146 b5 15. Ng5 (15. a4 b4 16. cxb4 cxb4 17. exf5 Qc8) 15... Qc8 16. exf5 Bxf5 17. Nde4 $6 Ng4 $6 (17... Bg6 18. Nxf6+ Bxf6 (18... exf6 19. Ne4 Qf5 20. f3) 19. Ne4 Bg7 20. f4) 18. Bh3 $16 (18. h3 Nh6 19. f4 Bg6 20. Qe2 Qd7 21. g4 f5 22. Nf2 fxg4 23. Ne6 gxh3 (23... g3 24. Ne4 Nf5 25. Nxf8 Rxf8 26. Ng5) 24. Bxh3 Bf5 25. Nxf8 Rxf8 26. Qh5) 18... Nh6 19. Rd2 Kh8 20. Bxf5 { Classic example "c1>>c8". c4,d5,e6 are fixed on the 's c8 color. Hope for salvation is only } (20. Re1 Bxh3 21. Nxd6 Bf5 22. Nxc8 Bxc2 23. Nxe7 Bf6 24. d6 Bxg5 25. Rxc2 Ng8) 20... Qxf5 21. Re1 Qg6 22. Nf3 Nf5 23. Qd1 (23. Qd3 $6 Rb8 24. Qf1 $6 {1-0 Bohatirchuk,F-Alatortsev,V/Leningrad 1934/URS-ch (31)} h5 $5 {The sharpest line where White marks better score. (58%).} 25. Qg2 {The calmest solid continuation in which White also has good score (54%).} {Bulgarian ICCF GM Nikolay Ninov resuscitated successfuly} Rg8 $5 26. h3 Bh6 27. Rde2 Bf4 28. Kh1) 23... Rb8 24. Rde2 Rb7 25. Kg2 (25. h3 $17) 25... h5 26. h4 (26. h3 $2 Bh6 27. Kh2) 26... Bh6 27. Neg5 f6 28. Ne4 Rg8 29. Ned2 Bf4 30. Kh1 Rg7 {} (30... Bxg3 31. fxg3 {½-½ Shirov,A-Timman,J/Wijk aan Zee 2003/CBM 93_01 (38)} Nxg3+ $1 {Knaak} 32. Kh2 Nxe2 33. Qxe2) (30... Nxg3+ $1 31. fxg3 Qxg3 32. Rg1 Qh3+ 33. Nh2 {Lilienthal-Levenfish/Moscow/1936}) 31. Rg1 $6 Bh6 32. Qf1 Rb8 33. Qh3 Rbg8 34. Rge1 Qh7 35. Nf1 Rg4 36. N3h2 Rc4 37. Nf3 b4 38. cxb4 Rxb4 39. b3 Rbg4 (39... a5) 40. Re6 a5 41. Qg2 a4 42. N3h2 Rxh4 {More chanses to win gave:} 43. R6e4 $142 $1 $18 {Only as ilustration:} (43. Qf3 Nd4 {½-½ Karjakin,S-Barsov,A/Hastings 2003/CBM 93_01 (22)}) (43. gxh4 Rxg2 44. Kxg2 Nxh4+ 45. Kh3 Ng6) 43... axb3 $140 44. axb3 Rxe4 45. Qxe4 Rb8 46. Nf3 (46. Qa4 Qf7 47. Rd1 Nd4) 46... Rxb3 47. Kg2 $1 Qg6 48. Nh4 Nxh4+ 49. Qxh4 Rb4 50. Qh3 Re4 (50... Qg4 51. Rxe7 {'½-½ Singer,K-Adamski,M/Laczna 2002/CBM 89 ext (25)'} Qxh3+ 52. Kxh3 Rd4 {½-½ Singer,K-Adamski,M/Laczna 2002/CBM 89 ext (25)} 53. Re6 Rxd5 54. Rxf6 Kg7 55. Re6 c4 {Oll,L-Dolmatov,S/Groningen 1993/CBM 39/½-½ (54)}) 51. Qc8+ Kh7 52. Ra1 Qg4 53. Qe8 $18 Qg8 $142 $1 54. Qc6 (54. Qxh5 Re5) 54... Rd4 $16 55. Re1 $1 Qxd5+ 56. Qxd5 $11 Rxd5 $5 57. Rxe7+ Kg6 58. Nh2 Rd1 59. Nf3 (59. f4 Bf8 60. Rd7 c4 {Rodriguez,R-De la Villa Garcia,J/Alcobendas 1993/EXT 98/0-1 (62)}) 59... Bg5 1/2-1/2


