1. c4 {Atlas,V Atlas,V Atlas,V Atlas,V: 'Atlas,Valeri Atlas,Valeri: 'Atlas,V''} e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e4 Bb4 (4... Bc5 5. Nxe5 Nxe5 6. d4 Bb4 7. dxe5 Nxe4 8. Qd4 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Be7 10. Qg4 g6 11. Bh6 d6) 5. d3 d6 6. g3 O-O (6... Bc5 7. Bg2 Nd4 $140 $2 8. Nxd4 Bxd4 {is another option here:} 9. Ne2 Bb6 10. d4 exd4 11. Nxd4 Ng4 12. O-O Qf6 13. Nf5 Ne5 14. Ne3 c6 15. Rb1 O-O 16. b3 a5 17. h3) 7. Bg2 a6 (7... Bc5 $1 {(threatening 14.e6)}) 8. O-O Bc5 {A rare move, aiming at preventing the advance of the g-pawn.} 9. h3 h6 10. Be3 Be6 (10... Bxe3 {e5, with good counterplay.} 11. fxe3 {allows White to develop dangerous initiative:}) 11. b3 Nd7 12. d4 exd4 13. Nxd4 {Threatening 14.g2-g4.} Nxd4 14. Bxd4 Qg5 $6 15. f4 Qf6 16. Bxc5 Nxc5 17. Qd2 Rad8 18. Rfe1 c6 19. Rac1 Bc8 {A dubious sacrifice.} 20. Red1 Rfe8 21. Qd4 Qxd4+ 22. Rxd4 Kf8 23. Rcd1 {The most natural continuation. Opening the g-file, White develops dangerous attack on the kingside.} Ke7 24. R4d2 a5 25. Kf2 $1 {Again the best move. In the occuring ending White has better chances.} Be6 26. f5 Bc8 27. g4 {[%mdl 4096]} g5 (27... Rd7) 28. e5 Kf8 (28... dxe5 $5 {Now} 29. f6+ {fails to 16...fe4}) 29. exd6 Re5 {Threatening ...f3.} 30. Ne2 Bd7 $6 {Again, 30...a5 was to be preferred.} (30... Ne4+ 31. Bxe4 Rxe4 32. d7) 31. Ng3 $1 {[%csl Rb4,Rc4][%cal Gd4b2,Gg4b4]} f6 $6 {This exchange significantly simplifies White's task. 31...c8 or 31...a5 was more stubborn.} 32. Bf3 Rde8 33. Re2 Kf7 34. Rxe5 Rxe5 35. Ne2 h5 36. Nd4 {[%csl Rb7,Rf7][%cal Ge4d6,Gd6f7,Ge4g5,Gd6b7]} h4 37. a3 Na6 38. Rb1 Nc5 39. Rd1 Na6 40. Rd2 Re8 41. Nc2 Re5 {Black resigned, as after} 42. b4 axb4 43. axb4 Ke8 {White promotes his pawn.} {If} 44. c5 {then} Kd8 $18 45. Be2 $6 Nxb4 46. Nxb4 Rxc5 {Yet,} 47. Ke1 {was a better choice.} Be8 48. Nd3 $40 Rc3 $6 {is strongly met by} 49. Nf2 Re3 {is elegantly refuted by} 50. Rd3 $1 Re5 51. Rd4 b5 52. Re4 Rd5 53. Re6 b4 {was to be preferred.} 54. Ne4 $1 1-0


