1. e4 {Ftacnik,Lubomir Ftacnik Ftacnik,Lubomir Ftacnik,Lubomir: 'Ftacnik'} c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. d3 d6 6. Be3 Rb8 7. Qd2 b5 8. Nge2 (8. f4 b4 9. Nd1 e6 10. Nf3 Nd4 11. O-O Ne7 12. Nh4 f5 (12... O-O 13. c3 bxc3 14. bxc3 Nb5 15. a4 Nc7 16. d4 cxd4 17. Bxd4 Bxd4+ 18. cxd4 f5) 13. c3 bxc3 14. bxc3 Ndc6 15. exf5 exf5 16. g4 O-O 17. gxf5 Bxf5) 8... b4 9. Nd1 Nd4 10. O-O e6 11. f4 (11. Nc1 Ne7 (11... a5) 12. a3 (12. c3 bxc3 13. bxc3 Ndc6 14. Bh6 (14. d4 cxd4 15. cxd4 O-O 16. Nb3 a5 17. Nc3 Rb4)) 12... a5 13. axb4 axb4 14. c3 bxc3 15. bxc3 Ndc6) (11. c3 bxc3 12. bxc3 Nxe2+ 13. Qxe2 Ba6 14. f4 Ne7) 11... Ne7 {Moves like these in a very charged positions can be truly dangerous, since instead of developing extra piece black is simply throwing more oil into the fire.} 12. g4 f5 13. gxf5 Nxe2+ (13... exf5 14. Ng3 h5 15. c3 bxc3 16. bxc3 h4 17. Ne2 Nxe2+ 18. Qxe2) 14. Qxe2 exf5 15. a3 (15. e5 O-O 16. d4 (16. exd6 Qxd6 17. Qf2 Bd4 $16) 16... cxd4 17. Bxd4 Bb7 $11) (15. exf5 Bxf5 16. Re1 O-O 17. Bxc5 dxc5 $36 18. Qxe7 Bd4+ (18... Qd4+ 19. Kh1) 19. Kh1 Qxe7 20. Rxe7 Rfe8 21. Bd5+ Kh8 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 23. c3 Re1+ $40 24. Kg2 Rg1+ $1 $17 25. Kf3 Bg4+ 26. Ke4 Re1+) 15... b3 (15... a5 16. axb4 $18 axb4 17. exf5 $18 Bxf5 $6 18. Ra7) 16. c3 $1 (16. cxb3 Rxb3) 16... O-O 17. Re1 (17. Qd2 Bb7 (17... Ba6 18. Re1) 18. Nf2 Qb6 $18) 17... g5 $2 {It is easy to understand Nakamura's wish to save his extra exchange, but this move loses. In comparison 17...xf6 seems good enough for the full equality.} 18. Nf2 (18. fxg5 f4 $1 19. Bf2 Ng6 20. h4 (20. Qh5 Ne5 (20... f3 21. Bxf3 Nf4 22. Qh4 Nxd3 23. Re3 $18) 21. d4 Bg4 22. Qh4 Nf3+ $15 23. Bxf3 Bxf3 24. dxc5 dxc5 25. Bxc5 Rb5 26. Qf2 Qxg5+ $3 27. Kf1 Qh5) 20... Ne5 21. Bf3 (21. Qd2 Ba6 22. d4 Nd3 23. Rf1 f3 24. Bh1 Qd7) 21... Qd7 22. d4 (22. Rf1 Ba6 $11 23. c4 Qh3 24. Be1 Nxf3+ 25. Rxf3 Bd4+ 26. Bf2 Qxh4 $17) 22... Ba6) 18... gxf4 19. Bxf4 Ng6 (19... fxe4 $18 20. Bg5) 20. Bd2 Qh4 21. d4 $6 cxd4 22. cxd4 fxe4 23. Bxe4 (23. Qc4+ $1 Kh8 24. Nxe4 d5 25. Qxd5 $18 Bb7 26. Qg5 (26. Qa5 Rbe8 27. d5 Bd4+ 28. Kh1 Be5 29. h3 Nf4) 26... Bxd4+ 27. Be3 Bxb2) 23... Bb7 24. Bxb7 Rxb7 25. Be3 $2 {[%mdl 8192] Ashley has lost control of the game few moves ago, but this natural retreat is a real losing blunder.} Re7 $1 26. Qd2 $1 (26. Kh1 Rxe3 $16) 26... Rf3 27. Rac1 (27. Kg2 Rfxe3) (27. Bg5 Rxe1+ 28. Rxe1 Rxf2 $14 29. Qxf2 Qxg5+) 27... Rfxe3 28. Rxe3 Qg5+ 29. Ng4 Qxg4+ 30. Rg3 Bxd4+ 31. Kh1 Qe4+ 32. Rg2 Be3 33. Rc8+ Kf7 34. Qd1 Nf4 35. Qxb3+ $11 d5 0-1


