1. e4 {Mikhalevski,V Mikhalevski,V Mikhalevski,V Mikhalevski,V: 'Mikhalevski,Victor Mikhalevski,Victor: 'Mikhalevski,V''} c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7 {Favourite continuation of A.Miles.Black has been preparing ge7 followed by d5.} 6. Be2 $146 {This move is already a novelty.White usually preferes 6.e3 or 6.:c6(Kasparov-Leko,Tilburg 1997).See my comments of Van der Wiel-Ernst,1998 in CBM66.} a6 7. O-O Nf6 8. Be3 Bb4 $1 {[%cal Gc6d4]} 9. Na4 Be7 10. Nxc6 (10. c4) 10... bxc6 11. Nb6 Rb8 12. Nxc8 Qxc8 $5 13. e5 $6 Nd5 14. Bc1 Bc5 15. Bd3 (15. c4 Ne7 16. b3 Qc7 17. Bb2 Ng6) (15. Qd3 Qc7 16. Qe4 (16. Qc4 Ba7 17. Qe4 O-O 18. Bxa6 f5 19. exf6 Rb4 20. Qe2 Nxf6) 16... a5 17. c4 Ne7 18. Kh1 O-O 19. Bd3 Ng6 20. f4 d6) (15. Qd3) (15. Kh1 O-O 16. Bd3 a5 17. Qh5 g6 18. Qe2 Qc7 19. c3 f6 20. Bh6 Rf7 21. exf6 Nf4 22. Bxf4 Qxf4 23. g3 Qxf6 24. f4 Rbf8 25. Rae1 Bb6 26. Qg4 Kh8 27. h4 Rg8 28. Kg2 h5 29. Qd1 Bc7 30. Qc2 Kg7 31. Re4 Qe7 32. Rfe1 Rf6 33. R1e2 Rgf8 34. b4 axb4 35. cxb4 d5 36. R4e3 Qxb4 37. Rxe6 Bxf4 38. Re7+ Kg8 39. Bxg6 Bxg3 40. Bf7+ Kh8 41. Re8 R6xf7 42. Qg6 Qf4 43. Rxf8+ Rxf8 44. Qxh5+ Kg7 45. Kh3 Bf2 46. Qg4+ Qxg4+ 47. Kxg4 d4 48. h5 Be3 49. Rc2 Rf4+ 50. Kg3 Rf6) 15... Qc7 $1 {[%csl Rd4][%mdl 32] Exchange of white-squared bishops is clearly in the Black's favour.} (15... O-O 16. c4 Ne7 17. b3 (17. Qc2 Ng6 18. b3 Bd4 19. Bb2 Bxb2 20. Qxb2 c5 21. f4 Qc7 22. Rad1 f6 23. Bxg6 hxg6 24. Rd6 fxe5 25. fxe5 Rxf1+ 26. Kxf1 Rf8+ 27. Kg1 Rf5) 17... Qc7 18. Bb2 Ng6 19. Qh5 Rfd8 20. Rad1 Qa5 21. Bb1 d5 22. cxd5 Rxd5 23. Rc1 Qb6 24. Qe2 Rbd8 25. Bc3 Bd4) 16. g3 (16. Qe2 Bd4 17. Re1 Bxb2 {[%csl Rf2][%cal Gc8a6,Gb8d8,Ge7f6] with some compensation.} 18. Bxb2 $143 Rxb2 $1 19. Bxa6 O-O $44 20. Bc4 $5 {[%cal Ge7g6,Gg6e5]} (20. Bd3 f5 21. Qd2 Ra8 22. Bc4 Qa5 23. Qxa5 Rxa5 24. Bb3 Nb6 25. Rad1 Kf8 26. c4 Ke7 27. f4 Na4 28. Rb1 Rxb1 29. Rxb1 Nc5 30. Kf2 g5 31. fxg5 Ne4+ 32. Ke3 Nxg5 33. Kf4 Nf7 34. Re1 Nh8 35. Kg5 Ng6 36. Kh6 Nxe5 37. Kxh7 Kf6 38. h4 d6 39. c5 Ra7+ 40. Kg8 Rg7+ 41. Kf8 Re7 42. Rxe5 dxe5 43. h5 e4 44. h6 Rb7) 20... Rb4 $5 21. g3 f6 $5 $14 {[%mdl 16]} (21... Qa7 22. Bb3 f6 $14 {[%mdl 16] and White is slightly better in both cases thanks to an extra pawn on the king side.} 23. exf6 $2 Rxf6 24. a4 Rb8 $15 25. Qd2 $5 Ne7 $1 26. Bc4 Rbf8 $140 $6 27. Re2 Qc5 $2 28. Bb3 Nf5 29. c3 $1 {[%csl Re8]} {Now} Kh8 $6 {is not logical as Black gets well-known position without a tempo.} 30. a5 {In the 4...c5 line white's bishop is still on f1 at the same position.} d5 31. a6 Qa7 32. Bc2 Nd6 33. Qd4 c5 34. Qg4 c4 35. Rf1 g6 36. h4 Nb5 37. h5 Nxc3 38. Rd2 Kg7 39. Kg2 Nb5 40. hxg6 hxg6 41. f4 Qxa6 42. Rh1 Qa8 43. Qg5 d4+ 44. Kg1 d3 45. Rdh2 Qa7+ 46. Kf1 Qa1+ 47. Kg2 Qa8+ 48. Kf2 Qa7+ 49. Kf3 Qa8+ 50. Kg4 Qxh1 51. Rxh1 Rf5 52. Qh6+ Kf7 53. Qh7+) (21... f6 22. exf6 Rxf6 23. Bd3 c5 24. a4 Qa7 25. a5 Rd4 26. Rf1 Rb4 27. a6 Rb6 28. Qh5 g6 29. Qg5 Kg7 30. h4 h6 31. Qe5 d6 32. Qe2 h5 33. Rfe1 Rb4 34. Bc4 Nc7 35. Reb1 d5 36. Rxb4 cxb4 37. Bd3 Qd4 38. Rd1 e5 39. Bxg6 Rxf2 40. Rxd4 Rxe2 41. Bd3 Re1+ 42. Kf2 Rb1)) 16... Bd4 $1 {[%cal Ge7d5,Gd8d7][%mdl 32]} (16... Qxe5 17. c4) 17. c3 $6 (17. c4 $142 $1 Nb4 18. Be4 $1 {making d7-d5 difficult.} Bxe5 {Black can try to get counterplay at the price of a pawn.}) 17... Bxe5 $1 {[%mdl 32] The prolongation of the same strategy.} 18. Bxa6 O-O $1 $15 {[%csl Rd4,Re3][%cal Gf6f5,Gf5f4] By the series of strong moves Black takes initiative in his hands.} 19. Bd3 $4 {[%mdl 8192] After this careless move White loses by force.} f5 $19 {[%cal Gf5f4]} 20. Re1 (20. a4 $1 {[%cal Gc7c6]}) 20... Bd6 $1 {[%mdl 64] Perhaps White missed this strong intermediate move.Now all is over.} 21. Re2 $1 Kh8 22. Qc2 $1 c5 23. b3 (23. c4 Nb4 $11 24. Qc3 $5 Nxd3 25. Qxd3 Be5) 23... Nf6 24. f4 $19 (24. Bg5) 24... c4 25. Bxc4 $1 Ng4 26. Rg2 {[%cal Ge3f2]} (26. h3 Bc5+ 27. Kf1 Qc6) 26... Bc5+ 27. Kf1 $19 (27. Kh1 Qc6 {[%csl Rd4]} 28. h3 $5 (28. Bd2 Nf2+ $15 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Ge7h4]} 29. Kg1 $6 Ne4+ 30. Kf1 $6 (30. Kh1 Nxg3+ $15 31. hxg3 $4 Rf6 $18) 30... Nxg3+ 31. Rxg3 Qh1+) (28. a4 $142 Nf2+ $2 29. Kg1 $1 $16 Nd3+ $140 $2 30. Kh1 Ne1) 28... Rf6 (28... Nf2+ {[%csl Rd4]} 29. Kh2 Nxh3 $1 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gd8h4]})) 27... Qc6 28. Be2 $19 {winning an exchange.} (28. Qe2 $5 e5 29. h3 {[%cal Gd5d6]} (29. fxe5 Nxe5 30. Bd3 Nf3) 29... Rbe8 $1 {[%cal Ge7d5]} (29... Qh6 30. h4 $143 e4 31. a4) (29... exf4 30. Bxf4 Rbe8 $14 31. Qd1 Re1+ $14 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gd1h5,Gd1f3]} 32. Kxe1 $5 $14 Qxg2 33. Qe2 $1) 30. hxg4 $5 (30. Bb5 Qh6) 30... exf4 31. Bb5 Qh6 32. Rh2 Rxe2 33. Rxh6 Rf2+ 34. Ke1 $14 {[%csl Re6,Re7] /=} Re8+ 35. Kd1 $14 gxh6) 28... e5 $140 29. h3 (29. fxe5 f4 $5 {[%cal Ga4b3]} 30. gxf4) 29... Nf2 30. h4 (30. fxe5 Rbe8 (30... Nxh3 31. Rh2 Ng1 $18 32. Qd3 $4 Rbe8 $18 {[%cal Ge1e6]} 33. Bf4 $142 $5 d6 34. Bh5) 31. Bf4 Nxh3 $143 32. Rh2 Nxf4 33. gxf4 $15 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gf8e8,Gd5a2]} Qg6 $6 34. Rh1 $1 Qg3 $4) 30... Rbe8 31. fxe5 f4 32. gxf4 $19 (32. Bxf4 $142 Nh3 33. Qd2 $1 $11 Rxe5) 32... Nh3 {was necessary with chances to equalize.} 0-1


