1. d4 {Avrukh,B Avrukh,B} d5 2. Bg5 h6 3. Bh4 c6 4. e3 Qb6 5. Qc1 e5 6. Nf3 e4 7. Nfd2 Be7 (7... Be6 $6 8. c4 Nd7 9. Nc3 Ne7 10. f3 $1 (10. Bg3 {[%cal Gc4d5,Gc6d5,Rc3b5]} a6 11. h4 Nf5 12. Bf4 h5 13. Qc2 Be7 14. g3 O-O 15. Be2 g6 16. O-O-O Rfc8 17. Kb1 $14 {[%cal Gg3g4] 1-0 Miladinovic,I-Rublevsky,S/Tivat 1995/EXP 48 (40)}) 10... exf3 (10... f5 11. fxe4 fxe4 12. Be2 {[%cal Ge2h5]}) 11. gxf3 g5 12. Bf2 Bg7 13. Qc2 Rc8 {[%cal Gc6c5]} 14. c5 $1 Qd8 15. Bd3 b6 16. b4 f5 17. Nb3 O-O 18. h4 Ng6 19. hxg5 hxg5 20. O-O-O $36 {½-½ Ovetchkin,R-Lastin,A/St Petersburg RUS 1998 (64)}) (7... Ne7 8. c4 Nf5 9. Bg3 Nxg3 10. hxg3 Be6 11. Nc3 Nd7 12. Qc2 Be7 13. Rb1 Nf6 14. b4 O-O 15. a3 h5 $11 {[%cal Gg7g6,Gg8g7] ½-½ Miladinovic,I-Degerman,L/Malmoe 1998 (49)}) 8. Bg3 Nf6 9. h3 $2 {[%mdl 8] Superfluous move in this variation,which could cost for white a lot.There is no idea for black to attack white's bishop on g3 with Nh5,black simply hasn't time for this.On the other hand it's a very serious lose of tempo for white.} (9. c4 O-O 10. Nc3 Be6 11. Be2 Qd8 12. O-O a6 {½-½ Knezevic,B-Horvath,I/Budapest 1994/EXT 94 (12)}) 9... O-O 10. c4 (10. Be2) 10... c5 $1 {No wonder, that black wants to punish white for their unaccurate play in the opening.} (10... Be6 {was also good} 11. Be2 (11. Nc3 $6 Nh5 12. Bh2 f5 $36 {[%cal Gf5f4]}) 11... Qd8 $11) 11. dxc5 Bxc5 (11... Qxc5 12. Nc3 Be6 13. cxd5 Bxd5 14. Nxd5 Qxd5 15. Bc4 Qd7 $11) 12. Nc3 {[%csl Rd5,Re4][%cal Gc3a4]} Bd7 $5 {[%cal Gd5d4]} (12... d4 {was leading to equality,but black wants more...} 13. Na4 (13. exd4 $143 Bxd4 14. Nb3 Nc6 $15) 13... Qb4 14. Nxc5 dxe3 15. Ncb3 (15. fxe3 Qxc5 16. Nb3 Qh5 $1 17. Be2 Qg6 $15) 15... exd2+ 16. Qxd2 Nc6 17. Be2 Bf5 18. Qxb4 (18. O-O Qxd2 19. Nxd2 Nd4 20. Bd1 Rfd8 $15) 18... Nxb4 19. O-O Rfd8 $11 {[%cal Gb4d3]}) 13. cxd5 (13. Nxd5 $2 Nxd5 14. cxd5 Bxe3 $17) 13... Bxe3 {[%mdl 512]} 14. fxe3 Qxe3+ 15. Ne2 Rc8 16. Qd1 $2 (16. Nc4 $143 $2 Qd3 17. Bxb8 $8 Raxb8 (17... Rxc4 $2 18. Nc3 $18) 18. Nc3 Qg3+ 19. Kd1 {[%cal Gc1e3]} b5 20. Qe3 Qh4 {[%cal Gf6g4]} 21. Nd6 (21. g3 Qh5+ 22. Be2 Bg4 $1 23. Nd2 $140 Rxc3 $1 24. bxc3 Nxd5 $19) 21... Ng4 22. Qe1 Nf2+ 23. Ke2 Rxc3 24. bxc3 e3 $40 {[%csl Rd6,Re2][%cal Gh4f4]}) (16. Qb1 $8 Na6 (16... Nxd5 $2 17. Qxe4) 17. Bf4 Qb6 18. Nc3 e3 19. Nc4 (19. Nb3 Nb4) 19... Rxc4 20. Bxc4 Qd4 21. O-O e2+ 22. Rf2 Qxc4 $44) 16... Na6 {[%cal Ga6b4,Gb4d3,Ga6c5,Gc5d3]} 17. Bf4 (17. Qb3 Nxd5 18. Qxe3 (18. Qxd5 Nb4) 18... Nxe3 19. Nd4 Nb4 20. Rb1 Nf5 $1 21. Nxf5 Bxf5 $36 {[%cal Ge4e3]}) (17. Nb3 Nb4 18. Bf4 Qb6 {leads to the game}) 17... Nb4 18. Nb3 {[%mdl 64]} Qb6 {Avrukh,B: 'leads to the game'} (18... Nd3+ $2 19. Qxd3 Qxd3 20. Ned4 {[%csl Rd3]} Qxd4 21. Nxd4 Nxd5 22. Bd6 $16) 19. Nc3 g5 20. a3 Nd3+ 21. Bxd3 exd3 22. Bd2 Rxc3 $5 ({Simple} 22... Re8+ 23. Kf1 Re5 {[%cal Ge5f5] was also very strong.} 24. g4 $8 Nxd5 (24... Rae8) 25. Rh2 Rae8 $17) 23. bxc3 (23. Bxc3 $2 Qe3+ 24. Kf1 d2 $1 $19 {[%cal Gd7b5,Gf6e4]}) 23... Re8+ 24. Kf1 Re2 $2 (24... Ba4 $1 25. Qf3 (25. Rb1 Ne4 26. Be1 d2 $19 {and black wins easily}) 25... Bxb3 26. Re1 (26. Qxd3 Re4 $19 {[%cal Gb3c4]}) 26... Rxe1+ 27. Bxe1 (27. Kxe1 Bxd5 28. Qxd3 Bxg2 29. Be3 Qe6 30. Rh2 Bxh3 $19) 27... Bc4 28. Bd2 Qb1+ 29. Kf2 Qxh1 30. Qxf6 Qd1 $19) (24... Ne4 25. Nd4 Ng3+ 26. Kg1 Ne2+ 27. Kf1 (27. Kf2 $2 Nxd4 28. cxd4 Re2+ $17) 27... Ng3+ $11) 25. Nd4 Ne4 26. Be1 Qf6+ $2 {[%mdl 8192] In fact only this move is losing, so nice game for black.Even here black have had good possibility to continue intiative:} (26... Bb5 $1 {[%cal Gd3d2]} 27. Kg1 (27. Nxb5 $2 Qxb5 $19 {[%csl Rf1]}) 27... d2 28. Bxd2 Rxd2 29. Qe1 (29. Qf3 Nxc3 $1 30. Qxc3 Rxd4 $17 {[%csl Rg1]}) 29... Bd3 $5 {[%cal Gb6b2]} (29... Rxd4 $11) 30. Rd1 Re2 31. Qf1 Nd2 32. Qxe2 Bxe2 33. Rxd2 Bc4 $15) 27. Kg1 Nf2 28. Qxe2 (28. Qb3 Nxh1 29. Nxe2 dxe2 30. Kxh1 $18) 28... dxe2 29. Bxf2 $18 {[%mdl 1024]} Qe5 30. Re1 (30. c4 Bf5 31. Re1 Bd3 32. Nf3 $18) 30... f5 31. c4 Qc7 32. Rxe2 Qxc4 33. Kh2 Qxd5 34. Rc1 f4 35. Kg1 h5 36. Nf3 g4 37. Rd2 Qb5 38. hxg4 hxg4 39. Ne5 Bf