1. e4 {Atlas,V Atlas,V Atlas,V Atlas,V: 'Atlas,Valeri Atlas,Valeri: 'Atlas,V''} c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. Nc3 d6 6. Be3 Nf6 7. f3 b5 8. Qd2 h5 {A rare move, aiming at preventing the advance of the g-pawn.} 9. O-O-O (9. a4 {is an interesting altermative:} b4 10. Na2 e5 11. Nb3 a5 12. Bb5+ Bd7 13. c3 bxc3 14. Nxc3 Bxb5 15. axb5 Nbd7 16. O-O Be7 17. Qf2 O-O 18. Ra4 Nc5 19. Nxc5 dxc5 20. Bxc5 Bxc5 21. Qxc5 Nd7 22. Qf2 Nb6 23. Raa1 Qc7 24. Rfd1 {1-0 Olivier,J-Ivanov,M/Cannes 1995/CBM 46 ext (56)}) 9... Nbd7 10. Bd3 Bb7 11. Rhe1 (11. f4 {is another option here:} b4 12. Nce2 e5 13. Nf3 Qc7 14. Ng5 Rc8 15. Kb1 Be7 16. h3 Nc5 17. Ng3 g6 18. h4 exf4 19. Bxf4 O-O 20. Rhe1 Nxd3 21. cxd3 a5 22. Be3 Ng4 23. Bd4 Ba6 24. Rf1 a4 25. Ne2 d5 26. exd5 Bd6 27. Ne4 b3 28. Bc3 Rfe8 29. Nd4 Be5 30. Nc6 Bxc3 31. Qxc3 {0-1 Van Laatum,G-Bosboom,M/Groningen 1995/CBM 50 ext (43)}) 11... Be7 12. Kb1 Rc8 (12... Nb6 {allows White to develop dangerous initiative:} 13. Qf2 $1 {(threatening 14.e6)} Nfd7 14. Qg3 g6 $140 $2 15. Nxe6) 13. h3 {Threatening 14.g2-g4.} h4 14. Bf2 Ne5 $6 (14... Nb6 $1 15. f4 b4) (14... Nc5 15. a3 g5 $5 {Now} 16. Qxg5 {fails to 16...fe4} (16. Be3 Nfd7 {e5, with good counterplay.})) 15. f4 Nc4 16. Bxc4 Rxc4 17. Qd3 Qc8 18. e5 dxe5 19. fxe5 Rxc3 {A dubious sacrifice.} (19... Nd7 {is elegantly refuted by} 20. Nxe6 $1 fxe6 21. Qg6+ Kf8 (21... Kd8 22. Bb6+) 22. Rf1) (19... Nd5 {was to be preferred.}) 20. bxc3 Nd5 21. Ne2 (21. Kb2 $6 {is strongly met by} Nb6) 21... Qc7 22. Bd4 O-O 23. g3 {The most natural continuation. Opening the g-file, White develops dangerous attack on the kingside.} Rc8 (23... hxg3 24. Nxg3 $40) 24. gxh4 b4 25. c4 $1 {Again the best move. In the occuring ending White has better chances.} Qxc4 26. Qxc4 Rxc4 27. h5 {[%mdl 4096]} Bg5 28. Rg1 Bh6 29. Rg4 Ne7 {Threatening ...f3.} ({Yet,} 29... a5 {was a better choice.}) 30. Rd3 Nf5 $6 {Again, 30...a5 was to be preferred.} 31. Ng3 $1 {[%csl Rb4,Rc4][%cal Gd4b2,Gg4b4]} Nxd4 $6 {This exchange significantly simplifies White's task. 31...c8 or 31...a5 was more stubborn.} 32. Rdxd4 Rc5 33. Rd8+ Kh7 34. Rxb4 Bg5 35. Rf8 Rc7 36. Ne4 {[%csl Rb7,Rf7][%cal Ge4d6,Gd6f7,Ge4g5,Gd6b7]} Be7 ({If} 36... Bf4 {then} 37. Nd6 $18 (37. Nf6+ $6 gxf6 38. Rxf4 Kg7)) 37. Rxf7 a5 38. Rd4 Kh6 39. Nd6 Bg2 40. Rg4 Bxd6 41. Rxc7 Bxh3 ({Black resigned, as after} 41... Bxh3 42. exd6 Bxg4 43. d7 {White promotes his pawn.}) 1-0


