1. e4 {Kostakiev,D Kostakiev,D Kostakiev,D Kostakiev,D Kostakiev,D: 'Kostakiev,Dimitar Kostakiev,Dimitar: 'Kostakiev,D''} e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 c5 5. a3 ({Bulgarian ICCF GM Nikolay Ninov resuscitated successfuly} 5. Qg4 $5) 5... Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Ne7 7. Qg4 $5 {Bohatirchuk 1934. Long years Botvinnik and Fischer kept different opposit oppinions about the line starting with 3...b4. Finaly In tom 3 of his splendid last books Botvinik recgnized that 7.g4! is giving advantage to White. Statistic confirmed - 56%:44%. Besides it two other variations draws attention:} (7. h4 $5 {The sharpest line where White marks better score. (58%).}) (7. Nf3 {The calmest solid continuation in which White also has good score (54%).}) 7... O-O (7... cxd4 $1 {Knaak} 8. Qxg7 (8. cxd4 $2 Qc7 9. Qd1 Qc3+ $17) 8... Rg8 9. Qxh7 Qc7 $1 10. Ne2 Nbc6 11. f4 Bd7 12. Qd3 {Lilienthal-Levenfish/Moscow/1936}) (7... Qa5 $6 8. Bd2 Qa4 $6 {1-0 Bohatirchuk,F-Alatortsev,V/Leningrad 1934/URS-ch (31)}) 8. Bd3 Nbc6 (8... Qa5 9. Bd2 Nbc6 10. Qh5 h6 11. g4 {½-½ Karjakin,S-Barsov,A/Hastings 2003/CBM 93_01 (22)}) (8... f5 9. exf6 Rxf6 10. Bg5 Rf7 11. Qh5 g6 12. Qd1 Nbc6 {½-½ Shirov,A-Timman,J/Wijk aan Zee 2003/CBM 93_01 (38)}) 9. Qh5 Ng6 10. Nf3 Qc7 11. O-O c4 12. Bxg6 (12. Be2 f6 13. exf6 Rxf6 14. Bg5 Nf4 {Oll,L-Dolmatov,S/Groningen 1993/CBM 39/½-½ (54)}) 12... fxg6 13. Qh3 (13. Qh4 Bd7 14. Bd2 Rf5 {'½-½ Singer,K-Adamski,M/Laczna 2002/CBM 89 ext (25)'} 15. Ng5 h6 16. Nf3 {½-½ Singer,K-Adamski,M/Laczna 2002/CBM 89 ext (25)}) 13... h6 14. a4 $146 (14. Qg4 Qf7 15. Ne1 Bd7 16. Qe2 g5 17. Rb1 b6 18. Bd2 Ne7 {Rodriguez,R-De la Villa Garcia,J/Alcobendas 1993/EXT 98/0-1 (62)}) 14... g5 15. Qg4 Qf7 16. h4 gxh4 17. Bxh6 $6 (17. Nxh4 $5) 17... Ne7 $6 (17... h3 $1 18. Be3 hxg2 $11) 18. Nxh4 $16 Nf5 19. Bc1 (19. Bg5 $142 $1 Nxh4 20. Qxh4 $16) 19... Nxh4 20. Qxh4 { Classic example "c1>>c8". c4,d5,e6 are fixed on the 's c8 color. Hope for salvation is only } Qg6 21. Ba3 Re8 22. Ra2 Bd7 23. Bd6 Qf5 24. f4 Qh7 25. Qg5