1. Nf3 d5 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. Qc2 Na6 7. O-O (7. a3 c5 8. O-O (8. dxc5 {1-0 Meins,G-Lagunow,A/Berlin/1993/ (37)} Qa5+ (8... Nxc5 9. b4 Nce4) 9. Nbd2)) 7... Nb4 (7... c5 8. cxd5 exd5 9. dxc5 Nxc5 10. Nc3 {½-½ Grigore,G-Herrera,I/Linares/1999/ (62)} Be6 11. Rd1 Rc8 12. Be3 Qa5 13. Nd4) 8. Qb3 (8. Qd1 dxc4 9. Na3 {½-½ Dannehr,J-Schimmel,B/FRG-chT qual corr 1991/ (27)} c5 10. Nxc4 b5 11. Nfe5 Nfd5 12. a3 bxc4 13. axb4 cxd4 14. Nxc4 {½-½ Sinkovics,P-Vegh,E/Hungary/1998/ (55)} (14. Nc6 Qc7 15. Nxe7+ Qxe7 16. Qxd4 Bb7 17. Qxc4) 14... Bf6 15. Bf4 Re8 16. Bd6 Bb7 (16... Ba6 17. Rxa6 Qc8 18. Qa4 Qxc4 19. Rxa7 Rad8 {½-½ Meins,G-Coenen,N/Groningen/1998/ (41)}) 17. Bc5 Qb8) 8... dxc4 9. Qxc4 b5 (9... Qd5 10. Nbd2 (10. Qxc7 Bd6 11. Qc3 Nxa2) 10... c5 11. dxc5 Qxc5 {½-½ Pyrich,G-McGowan,P/SCO-ch corr/1992/ (26)} 12. a3 Nbd5 {0-1 Vasile,C-Modena,G/EU-chT4 corr8896/ 1988/ (22)} 13. Ne5 Qd6 14. Ndf3 Nd7 15. Bf4 Nxf4 16. gxf4 Nb6 17. Qb3 Bd7) 10. Qb3 (10. Qxb5 Ba6 (10... Nc2 11. Qc6) 11. Qa4 $19 Bxe2 12. Re1 Bb5 13. Qxb5 Nc2 14. Nc3 Nxa1 15. Qe2) 10... a5 (10... Bb7 $17 11. a3 $5 Bd5 12. Qd1 Nc6 13. Nc3 b4 $11 14. Nxd5 $2 exd5 $16 15. Qa4 Qe8 $13 16. axb4 Nxb4 $15 17. Bd2 $2 a5 18. Rfc1) 11. Nc3 Rb8 (11... a4 12. Qd1) 12. Bf4 (12. a4 bxa4 13. Qxa4 $15 Bb7) 12... a4 13. Qd1 Bb7 (13... Nbd5 14. Nxd5 Nxd5) 14. Rc1 (14. Nxb5 Bxf3 15. Bxc7 Qd7 16. Bxb8 Bxg2 17. Kxg2 Qxb5 $19) 14... Nbd5 15. Nxd5 Nxd5 16. Bd2 Nb6 17. Bf4 Rc8 (17... Nd5) (17... Bd6) 18. Qd3 b4 (18... c6 19. Ne5 $13 Nd5 $5 20. Bd2) (18... c5 $17 19. Qxb5 $2 Bc6 $19 (19... cxd4 20. Rxc8 Bxc8 21. Be5 $13) (19... c4 20. a3) 20. Qd3 Bxf3 $5 21. Bxf3 Qxd4 22. Qxd4 cxd4 $13 23. Be5 $5) 19. Ng5 Bxg5 20. Bxg5 Qxg5 {White has two pawns for the exchange, but his pieces lack coordination.} 21. Bxb7 Rb8 22. Rxc7 Nd5 23. Bxd5 Qxd5 (23... exd5 24. Rfc1) 24. b3 axb3 (24... Rfd8 25. Rc4) 25. axb3 e5 (25... Rfd8) 26. dxe5 Qxe5 {Black has achieved some success, white's pawn structure was compromised and black can generate attack against white king.} 27. Qc4 $6 Rb6 28. Rd1 Rf6 29. Rc8 Qe7 30. Qc7 (30. Ra1 g6 (30... Rd6 31. Rxf8+ $15 Qxf8 (31... Kxf8 32. Ra8+ Rd8 33. Rxd8+ $15 Qxd8 34. Qxb4+ $19) 32. Qxb4) 31. Raa8 Rxc8 32. Qxc8+ Kg7 $19 33. Qh8+ Kh6 $17 34. Re8 $5 Qd6 35. Re4 Rf5 36. Rh4+ Rh5 37. Rxh5+ gxh5 38. h4) (30. Rd4 Rb6 31. Rc7 Qf6 32. Rdd7) 30... Qxc7 31. Rxc7 g6 $6 (31... Rb6 32. Rdd7 g6) 32. Rb7 $2 {Shliperman misses his last chance for tactical complications.} Re8 33. e3 (33. e3 Re4 34. Rd8+ Kg7 35. Rdb8) 0-1


