1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. e3 (5. Bg5) 5... Ne4 (5... Bb7 6. Bd3 O-O (6... Ne4) 7. O-O $16) 6. Qc2 Bb7 7. Bd3 f5 8. O-O Bxc3 9. bxc3 $2 {[%mdl 8] Superfluous move in this variation,which could cost for white a lot.There is no idea for black to attack white's bishop on g3 with Nh5,black simply hasn't time for this.On the other hand it's a very serious lose of tempo for white.} O-O 10. Nd2 (10. Ne1) (10. c5 {[%csl Rd3]}) 10... Qh4 $1 {No wonder, that black wants to punish white for their unaccurate play in the opening.} 11. f3 Ng5 (11... Nxd2 12. Bxd2 $2 Nc6) 12. f4 {[%csl Rd5,Re4][%cal Gc3a4]} Nf7 $5 {[%cal Gd5d4]} (12... Nh3+ $2 13. gxh3 Qxh3 14. e4 $1 $19 {[%cal Gd7b5,Gf6e4]} {Simple} Rf6 15. Nf3 Rg6+ {[%cal Ge5f5] was also very strong.} 16. Ng5 $8) (12... Qg4 13. d5 Nf7 $17) 13. e4 Nh6 {[%mdl 512]} 14. Nf3 Qh5 15. Ba3 Re8 16. Rae1 $2 fxe4 {[%cal Ga6b4,Gb4d3,Ga6c5,Gc5d3]} 17. Rxe4 Ng4 18. d5 {[%mdl 64]} Na6 19. h3 Nf6 20. Re5 Qh6 21. Ng5 exd5 22. cxd5 Nc5 $5 23. Bxc5 bxc5 24. Qb3 (24. Rfe1 $17) 24... Rxe5 $2 25. fxe5 Bxd5 26. Bc4 c6 $2 {[%mdl 8192] In fact only this move is losing, so nice game for black.Even here black have had good possibility to continue intiative:} 27. exf6 Qxg5 28. Bxd5+ cxd5 (28... Qxd5 29. f7+ Kf8 $11 30. Qb1 $2 Qh5 31. Qd3) 29. f7+ $18 {[%mdl 1024]} (29. Qb7 Rf8 (29... Rd8 30. Qc7) 30. f7+ Kh8 31. Qxd7 $19 g6 32. Qd6 $19 {[%cal Gb3c4]} Kg7 33. Qxc5 Rxf7 34. Rxf7+ $19 {and black wins easily} Kxf7 35. Qxa7+) 29... Kf8 30. Qb7 Rd8 31. Qxa7 Qe7 (31... Qe3+) (31... d6 $19) (31... d4 32. cxd4 Qe3+) 32. a4 (32. Qb6) 32... Qd6 33. Kh1 (33. a5 Qc6 34. Rb1 Kxf7 35. Rb8) 33... Qc6 34. Rb1 Kxf7 35. Rb6 (35. Rb7) 35... Ra8 36. Rxc6 Rxa7 37. Rxc5 Ke6 38. a5 Kd6 39. Rb5 Kc6 40. Rb8 g6 41. Kg1 Rxa5 42. Rh8 Kb5 43. Rxh7 Kc4 44. Rxd7 Kxc3 $18 45. h4 d4 46. Kf2 Ra2+ 47. Kf3 $18 d3 $1 {[%cal Gd3d2]} 48. g4 Rh2 49. Kf4 Rxh4 50. Kg5 Rh3 $5 {[%cal Gb6b2]} 51. Kxg6 d2 52. Rxd2 Kxd2 53. g5 Ke3 54. Kf6 Rf3+ $15 55. Ke6 $11 Kf4 56. g6 $1 Kg5 57. g7 $17 {[%csl Rg1]} Rf6+ $2 58. Ke7 $19 {[%csl Rf1]} Rg6 $1 59. Kf7 Rxg7+ 60. Kxg7 1-0


