1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. g3 d5 (4... Bc5) 5. exd5 Nxd5 6. Bg2 Nxc3 7. bxc3 Be7 8. Qe2 (8. O-O O-O 9. Re1 Bf6) 8... O-O {A rare move, aiming at preventing the advance of the g-pawn.} 9. O-O (9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. Qxe5 Bf6 11. Qd5 Re8+ 12. Kf1 Qe7) 9... Bf6 10. d3 Bg4 (10... e4 11. Qxe4 Bxc3 12. Ng5 g6 13. Rb1) 11. Rb1 Rb8 12. Qe3 (12. h3 Be6 13. c4 (13. a4 Bd5 14. c4 Nd4 15. Nxd4 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 exd4) 13... a6) (12. Qe4 Qd7 13. Ng5 Bxg5 (13... Bf5 14. Qd5) 14. Bxg5 Bh3 {1-0 Olivier,J-Ivanov,M/Cannes 1995/CBM 46 ext (56)}) 12... Qd7 13. Re1 {Threatening 14.g2-g4.} (13. c4 Nd4 (13... Bh3 14. Bb2 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Rfe8 16. Nd2) 14. Nxd4 (14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. Qxe5 {0-1 Van Laatum,G-Bosboom,M/Groningen 1995/CBM 50 ext (43)} Nf3+ {is an interesting altermative:} 16. Bxf3 Bxf3 17. Bb2 f6 18. Qe3 Qc6) 14... exd4 15. Qf4 b6 (15... c6 16. Bxc6)) 13... Bh3 14. Bh1 (14. Nd2) 14... Rfe8 $6 15. Ng5 (15. Nd2 Nd4) 15... Bxg5 (15... Nd4 16. Rb2) 16. Qxg5 Be6 17. c4 (17. Rb2 Bd5 18. Bxd5 Qxd5 19. Qg4) 17... Nd4 18. Rb2 Bg4 19. Qe3 Qa4 {A dubious sacrifice.} (19... Qf5 {Yet,} 20. f4 {was a better choice.} (20. Bxb7 $1 Rxb7 21. Rxb7 Nf3+ (21... Bf3 22. Qxe5 $5 {Now}) 22. Kf1 (22. Kh1 Nxe1) 22... Nxh2+ 23. Kg1 Nf3+ {was to be preferred.} 24. Kf1 $1 Qh5) (20. Be4 {fails to 16...fe4} Qh5) (20. Rxb7 {e5, with good counterplay.} Rxb7 {allows White to develop dangerous initiative:} (20... Nxc2 21. Rxb8 Rxb8 22. Qxa7 Rf8 23. Be4 Qh5 24. Rf1 Nd4) 21. Qxd4 $1 {(threatening 14.e6)} Bf3 22. Bxf3 Qxf3 $140 $2 23. Rxe5 Rbb8 {is another option here:} 24. Bb2 f6 25. Rxe8+ Rxe8 26. Qd5+ Qxd5 27. cxd5 Re2 28. Bd4 a6) 20... Qh5 21. fxe5 $40 Ne2+ $6 {is strongly met by} 22. Rxe2 Bxe2 {is elegantly refuted by}) 20. f3 Bd7 21. Qf2 Bc6 22. c3 Ne6 ({If} 22... Nf5 {then} 23. Rbe2 $18 Qa5 $6 (23... f6 24. f4)) 23. Rxe5 {The most natural continuation. Opening the g-file, White develops dangerous attack on the kingside.} Nc5 24. Rxe8+ (24. Qxc5 Qd1+ 25. Kf2 Qxh1) ({Black resigned, as after} 24. Rxc5 Qd1+ 25. Kg2 Qxc1 {White promotes his pawn.}) 24... Rxe8 25. Rd2 $1 {Again the best move. In the occuring ending White has better chances.} Qa5 26. Bb2 (26. d4 Na4 (26... Qxc3 27. Bb2) 27. d5 {[%csl Rb7,Rf7][%cal Ge4d6,Gd6f7,Ge4g5,Gd6b7]} Qxc3 28. dxc6 Qxc1+ 29. Kg2 bxc6) 26... Qxa2 27. Qxc5 {[%mdl 4096]} Qb1+ 28. Kg2 Re1 29. Ba3 h6 {Threatening ...f3.} 30. Qf8+ Kh7 $6 {Again, 30...a5 was to be preferred.} 31. Qxf7 $1 {[%csl Rb4,Rc4][%cal Gd4b2,Gg4b4]} Rxh1 $6 {This exchange significantly simplifies White's task. 31...c8 or 31...a5 was more stubborn.} 32. Qf5+ Kh8 33. Qf8+ Kh7 34. Qf5+ Kh8 1-0


