1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 {Favourite continuation of A.Miles.Black has been preparing ge7 followed by d5.} 6. f3 $146 {This move is already a novelty.White usually preferes 6.e3 or 6.:c6(Kasparov-Leko,Tilburg 1997).See my comments of Van der Wiel-Ernst,1998 in CBM66.} Qb6 7. Nb3 e6 8. Qe2 (8. Bf4 $1 {[%cal Gc7c6]} Ne5 $142 $1 9. Qe2 a6 $1 {making d7-d5 difficult.} 10. Be3 {Black can try to get counterplay at the price of a pawn.} Qc7 11. f4 Ned7 12. a4 b6 13. g4 {[%csl Rf2][%cal Gc8a6,Gb8d8,Ge7f6] with some compensation.} Bb7 $143 14. Bg2 $1 h6 15. g5 $44 hxg5 $5 {[%cal Ge7g6,Gg6e5]} 16. fxg5 $5 Nh5 17. g6 $5 $14 {[%mdl 16]} Nhf6 18. gxf7+ Kxf7 $14 {[%mdl 16] and White is slightly better in both cases thanks to an extra pawn on the king side.} 19. O-O-O $2 Ne5 20. h4) 8... a6 $1 {[%cal Gc6d4]} 9. g4 (9. Be3 Qc7 10. g4 Be7 $15 11. O-O-O $4 b5 $18 12. Qf2 $142 Nd7 $2 13. h4 $1 $16 Nce5 $140 $2 14. Kb1 Rb8 15. g5 b4 16. Ne2 Nc4 17. h5 a5 18. Ned4 $11 Nde5 $5 19. Nd2 O-O 20. Nxc4) 9... h6 (9... Be7 10. h4 $14 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gd1h5,Gd1f3]} Qc7 $5 $14 11. Be3 b5 $1 12. O-O-O Bb7 13. Kb1 Rc8 14. g5 Nd7 {[%csl Rd4]} 15. Qf2 $5 Nce5 16. Nd4 {[%csl Rd4]} Nc4 17. Bh3 $1 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gd8h4]} b4 18. Nce2 $15 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Ge7h4]} Nc5 $6 19. Bc1 O-O $6 20. h5) 10. Be3 Qc7 11. O-O-O b5 12. Kb1 Ne5 $5 13. Qf2 $6 b4 (13... Nc4 $14) 14. Na4 Rb8 15. Rg1 Bb7 $1 {[%csl Rd4][%mdl 32] Exchange of white-squared bishops is clearly in the Black's favour.} 16. Bb6 (16. h4) 16... Qc6 $1 {[%cal Ge7d5,Gd8d7][%mdl 32]} 17. Ba7 $6 Ra8 $1 {[%mdl 32] The prolongation of the same strategy.} 18. Na5 Qxa4 $1 $15 {[%csl Rd4,Re3][%cal Gf6f5,Gf5f4] By the series of strong moves Black takes initiative in his hands.} 19. Nxb7 $4 {[%mdl 8192] After this careless move White loses by force.} Qd7 $19 {[%cal Gf5f4]} 20. Qb6 (20. Bxa6 Nc6) 20... Be7 $1 {[%mdl 64] Perhaps White missed this strong intermediate move.Now all is over.} (20... Nxf3 $143 21. Bxa6) 21. f4 $1 (21. Bxa6 O-O 22. Bb5 Bd8) 21... Nc6 22. Nc5 $1 Qxa7 23. Qxc6+ Kf8 24. g5 $19 (24. e5 dxe5 25. fxe5 Bxc5 $14 {[%csl Re6,Re7] /=} 26. exf6 Bxg1 $14) 24... Nh5 (24... dxc5 25. gxf6 $5 {[%cal Ga4b3]} Bxf6 26. Rd7 $5 Rd8 27. Qd6+ {[%cal Gd5d6]} Ke8 $1 {[%cal Ge7d5]} 28. Rxd8+ $5 Bxd8 29. Bxa6) (24... Qxc5 25. Qxa8+) 25. Nd7+ $1 Kg8 26. g6 {[%cal Ge3f2]} Nxf4 27. Bc4 $19 Nxg6 28. Bxe6 $19 {winning an exchange.} fxe6 $140 29. Rxg6 Rd8 30. Rxe6 (30. Rdg1 $4 Qxd7 $18 {[%cal Ge1e6]} (30... Bg5 $142 $5 31. Nb6 Qf7)) 30... Qxd7 31. Qd5 Kh7 (31... Kf8 32. Qf5+ Bf6 $143 33. Rxf6+ gxf6 34. Qxf6+ $15 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gf8e8,Gd5a2]} Kg8 $6 (34... Ke8 35. Qxh8+ $18) 35. Rg1+ $1 Kh7 $4 36. Qg6#) 32. Qf5+ $19 Kg8 {was necessary with chances to equalize.} 33. Qd5 $142 Kf8 34. Qf5+ $1 $11 Kg8 35. Qd5 0-1


