1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5 e6 7. Qd2 Qb6 8. Nb3 Be7 9. Bxf6 (9. h4 a6 10. h5 h6 11. Bxf6 gxf6 12. O-O-O Bd7 13. Rh3 O-O-O 14. Kb1 Kb8 15. Rd3 Rhg8 16. f4 Bc8 17. Qe1) (9. Be3 Qc7 10. f3 O-O 11. g4 a6 12. g5 Nd7 13. h4 b5 14. a3 Nde5 15. Be2 Rb8) 9... Bxf6 (9... gxf6 10. Be2 Bd7 11. O-O Ne5 12. a4 O-O 13. a5) 10. Qxd6 Be5 11. Qc5 (11. Qd2 O-O 12. Bd3 a5 13. a4 Rd8 14. f4 Bxc3 15. bxc3 e5 16. f5 Bxf5 17. Qf2 Qxf2+ 18. Kxf2 Bc8) 11... Qxc5 12. Nxc5 Ke7 13. Bb5 (13. O-O-O b6 14. Nd3 Bxc3 15. bxc3 Bb7 16. f3 Rac8 17. Kb2 Rc7 18. Nc1 (18. Nb4 Ne5 19. Ba6 Bxa6 20. Nxa6 Nc4+ 21. Kb3 Na5+ 22. Kb2 Nc4+) 18... Ne5 19. Bd3 Rhc8 20. Ne2) 13... Nd4 (13... Nb4 14. O-O-O) 14. O-O-O (14. Ba4 a6 (14... b6 15. Nd3 Bc7 16. O-O-O) 15. Nd3 Bc7 16. O-O-O (16. O-O) 16... b5 17. Bb3 Rd8 18. Kb1 a5 19. a4 Nxb3 (19... Rb8 20. Nxb5 Nxb5 21. axb5 Rxb5) 20. Nxb5) 14... Rd8 15. Bf1 (15. Nb3 Nxb3+ (15... Nxb5 16. Nxb5 Bd7 17. N5d4 Rac8 18. g3 (18. c3 Ba4 19. Nf3 Bf4+ 20. Kc2 Bc6 21. Rxd8 Rxd8 22. Re1) 18... Rc4 19. c3 Bc7 20. Rhe1 b5 21. Nc2 (21. Rd3) 21... Bb6 22. f3 Rdc8 23. Kb1 a5 24. a3 h5 25. Rd3 (25. Rd2)) 16. axb3 Rxd1+ 17. Rxd1 a6 18. Be2 Bd7 19. g3 Bc6 20. f3) (15. Bc4 a6 16. Nd3 Bc7 17. a3 b5 18. Ba2 a5 19. Nc5 b4 20. Nd5+ exd5 21. Rxd4 bxa3 22. bxa3 Bd6 23. Rxd5 Be6 24. Nxe6 Bxa3+ 25. Kd2 fxe6) 15... b6 16. Nd3 Bd6 (16... Bc7 17. g3 Bb7 18. Bg2) 17. Ne2 (17. e5 Bc7 18. Ne2 Nxe2+ (18... Nc6 19. f4 Bb7 20. Rg1) 19. Bxe2) 17... Nc6 (17... Nxe2+ 18. Bxe2 Bb7) (17... Bc7) 18. g3 Ba6 19. Nc3 Rac8 {Black king sits in the deep corner in order to enable this push in the moment, when e6 pawn is not completely protected.} 20. e5 (20. f4) 20... Bb8 21. f4 Nd4 22. Bg2 (22. Nb4 Bxf1 (22... Bb7 23. Ba6) 23. Rhxf1 Rc4 24. Na6) 22... Bxd3 23. Rxd3 Ne2+ 24. Kd2 Nxc3 25. Rxd8 Rxd8+ 26. Kxc3 g5 27. Be4 $2 {A terrible oversight in an unclear position. Black had to strive for compensation as white bishop' s pair could become very dangerous.} (27. Re1 gxf4 28. gxf4 f6) (27. fxg5 Bxe5+ 28. Kb3 Rg8 (28... Rd2 29. Be4) 29. Rd1 (29. Be4 Rxg5 30. Bxh7 f5) 29... Rxg5 30. Bc6 Bd6) 27... gxf4 28. gxf4 f6 29. exf6+ Kxf6 30. Bxh7 Rh8 (30... Bxf4 31. h4 Be5+ 32. Kb3 a5 33. a4 Rd4 34. c3) 31. Bd3 Rh3 32. Rf1 Rxh2 33. f5 Be5+ 34. Kb3 Rh4 35. fxe6+ Kxe6 36. Ba6 Rh7 37. a4 Kd6 $19 38. c3 Kc7 39. Rf8 $13 Re7 40. Kc4 $11 Kd6 41. Ra8 Bg7 42. Kd3 Rf7 43. Bb5 Bf6 44. Ke4 Bg5 45. Rg8 $15 Bc1 46. Rg2 $19 Re7+ 47. Kd3 Bf4 48. Rg8 $1 Rh7 49. Rc8 Rc7 50. Rd8+ $1 Ke7 51. Rd4 {0-1 Illescas Cordoba,M-Polgar,J/Dos Hermanas 1997/ (32)} Be5 $1 52. Rg4 Bf6 53. Ke4 Rc5 54. Rg8 Re5+ $14 55. Kd3 Rd5+ 56. Kc2 Rd8 $16 57. Rg2 Be5 58. Kb3 Rc8 59. Re2 Rc5 $16 60. Ka2 $6 Ke6 61. Ba6 Rc7 62. Kb3 Rh7 $1 63. Rd2 Rc7 64. Rd1 Rg7 65. Bc4+ Ke7 $14 66. Bd5 Kd6 67. Be4+ Kc7 68. Rf1 Re7 69. Ba8 Bg7 70. Kc4 Kb8 71. Bd5 Rc7+ 72. Kb4 Rd7 73. Rf5 Re7 74. Rf2 Rd7 75. Bc6 Re7 76. Rg2 Kc7 77. Bd5 Kd6 78. Bf3 Kc7 79. Kc4 Rf7 80. Bd5 Rf4+ 81. Kd3 Bf6 82. Be4 Kd6 83. Rg8 Rf2 84. Rf8 Ke6 85. b4 Rh2 86. Rc8 Rh3+ 87. Kc2 Rh2+ 88. Kb3 Rh3 89. Rc7 Be5 90. Rc6+ Kd7 91. Rc4 Re3 92. Bb7 Kd6 93. b5 Kd7 94. Bc8+ Ke7 95. Rc6 Kd8 96. Bf5 Rf3 97. Bg6 Ke7 98. Be4 Re3 99. Rc4 Bxc3 100. Rxc3 Rxe4 101. Rc7+ Kd6 102. Rxa7 Re3+ 103. Kc4 Re4+ 104. Kd3 Rh4 0-1


