1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5 e6 7. Qd2 a6 8. O-O-O h6 9. Be3 Be7 10. f4 Bd7 11. Be2 b5 12. Bf3 Rc8 13. Kb1 Na5 (13... Qc7 14. Nb3 Rb8 15. g4 b4 16. Ne2 g5 17. e5 dxe5 18. fxg5 hxg5 19. Bxg5 e4 20. Bxf6 Bxf6 21. Bxe4 Rb5 22. Ng3 Bg5 23. Qe2 Ne5 $44 {Oll,L-Lerner,K/URS-FL Kujbyshev 1986/- (97)}) 14. e5 $2 (14. g4 Nc4 15. Qf2 b4 16. Nce2 Qc7 17. g5 hxg5 18. fxg5 Nh7 19. h4 e5 20. Nf5 g6 21. Nxe7 Kxe7 22. Bc1 Be6 23. Ng3 Qa5 24. b3 Rc5 25. Rhf1 Rhc8 $2 (25... Rf8 $13) 26. Bg4 $1 $18 Na3+ 27. Bxa3 Rxc2 28. Rd2 Rxd2 29. Qxd2 Bxg4 30. Bxb4 Qb6 31. Bxd6+ Qxd6 32. Rxf7+ Ke6 33. Qxd6+ Kxd6 34. Rxh7 Rc3 35. Nf1 Be2 36. Kb2 Rh3 37. Nd2 Kc5 38. Rd7 {1-0 Short,N-Benjamin,J/Hastings8788 1987}) (14. Qd3 {0-1 Boudre,J-Shirov,A/Val Maubuee (04) ,EXT 89 1989} Qc7 15. Rhe1 b4 16. e5 bxc3 17. exf6 Bxf6 18. b3 d5 19. Bc1 O-O 20. g4 Bb5 21. Nxb5 axb5 22. g5 Nxb3 23. gxf6 Nxc1 24. Qe3 Qa5 25. Qxc1 Ra8 $13 {Kamsky,G-Atalik,S/Tilburg 1993/1-0 (66)}) (14. Qf2 Nc4 15. g4 g5 16. fxg5 hxg5 17. Bc1 b4 18. Nce2 e5 19. Nf5 Bxf5 20. gxf5 g4 21. Bg2 Qb6 22. Qxb6 Nxb6 23. c3 a5 24. cxb4 axb4 25. Ng3 $6) 14... dxe5 15. fxe5 Nc4 16. Qe1 Nxe5 17. Bb7 b4 $1 (17... Rb8 $15 {This continuation is well known and good for black .Therefor it is very interesting why Hjartarson went for it , and Eshley refrained from it ?} 18. Bxa6 b4 $5) 18. Bxc8 Qxc8 19. Bc1 $1 (19. Nce2 Nc4 20. Bc1 e5 $17 21. Nb3 Bf5 $2 {This move looks suspicious even without calculations ! Balck had a good compensation due to his pair of bishops , a pawn and an active position .}) 19... Neg4 $6 20. Nce2 e5 $142 (20... O-O $14 21. h3 Ne5 $1 $16 {Black probably had missed this move after which white's advantage is obvious .}) 21. h3 exd4 22. Nxd4 $140 $6 Qb7 23. hxg4 Bxg4 24. Rd3 Ne4 (24... O-O 25. Bxh6 $1 $13 gxh6 26. Rxh6 Qe4 $1) 25. Rf1 $18 O-O 26. Rf4 f5 27. Rxg4 fxg4 28. Re3 Nc3+ 29. bxc3 bxc3+ 30. Nb3 Bf6 31. Qe2 Qc8 (31... h5 32. Re8 $2) 32. Re6 h5 33. Rxa6 h4 34. Ra5 Re8 35. Qd3 Qc6 36. Rd5 Re1 (36... h3 $1 37. gxh3 gxh3 38. Rh5) 37. Qf5 Qe6 38. Qxe6+ Rxe6 39. a4 Re4 40. a5 Ra4 41. Bg5 Bxg5 42. Rxg5 Kf7 43. a6 g3 44. Na5 Rb4+ 45. Nb3 Ra4 46. Nc5 Ra5 47. Ne4 Rxa6 48. Nxc3 Rb6+ 49. Kc1 Rb4 50. Ne2 Kf6 51. Rh5 g5 52. Kd2 Kf5 53. Rh8 Ra4 54. Rf8+ Ke5 55. Re8+ Kf5 56. Rf8+ Kg4 57. Rd8 $2 h3 58. Rd3 h2 59. Rxg3+ 1-0


