1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 c5 5. a3 ({Bulgarian ICCF GM Nikolay Ninov resuscitated successfuly} 5. Qg4 $5) 5... Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Ne7 7. Qg4 $5 {Bohatirchuk 1934. Long years Botvinnik and Fischer kept different opposit oppinions about the line starting with 3...b4. Finaly In tom 3 of his splendid last books Botvinik recgnized that 7.g4! is giving advantage to White. Statistic confirmed - 56%:44%. Besides it two other variations draws attention:} (7. h4 $5 {The sharpest line where White marks better score. (58%).}) (7. Nf3 {The calmest solid continuation in which White also has good score (54%).}) 7... O-O (7... cxd4 $1 {Knaak} 8. Qxg7 (8. cxd4 $2 Qc7 9. Qd1 Qc3+ $17) 8... Rg8 9. Qxh7 Qc7 $1 10. Ne2 Nbc6 11. f4 Bd7 12. Qd3 {Lilienthal-Levenfish/Moscow/1936}) (7... Qa5 $6 8. Bd2 Qa4 $6 {1-0 Bohatirchuk,F-Alatortsev,V/Leningrad 1934/URS-ch (31)}) 8. Bd3 Nbc6 (8... Qa5 9. Bd2 Nbc6 10. Qh5 h6 11. g4 {½-½ Karjakin,S-Barsov,A/Hastings 2003/CBM 93_01 (22)}) (8... f5 9. exf6 Rxf6 10. Bg5 Rf7 11. Qh5 g6 12. Qd1 Nbc6 {½-½ Shirov,A-Timman,J/Wijk aan Zee 2003/CBM 93_01 (38)}) 9. Qh5 Ng6 10. Nf3 Qc7 11. O-O c4 12. Bxg6 (12. Be2 f6 13. exf6 Rxf6 14. Bg5 Nf4 {Oll,L-Dolmatov,S/Groningen 1993/CBM 39/½-½ (54)}) 12... fxg6 13. Qh3 (13. Qh4 Bd7 14. Bd2 Rf5 {'½-½ Singer,K-Adamski,M/Laczna 2002/CBM 89 ext (25)'} 15. Ng5 h6 16. Nf3 {½-½ Singer,K-Adamski,M/Laczna 2002/CBM 89 ext (25)}) 13... h6 14. a4 $146 (14. Qg4 Qf7 15. Ne1 Bd7 16. Qe2 g5 17. Rb1 b6 18. Bd2 Ne7 {Rodriguez,R-De la Villa Garcia,J/Alcobendas 1993/EXT 98/0-1 (62)}) 14... g5 15. Qg4 Qf7 16. h4 gxh4 17. Bxh6 $6 (17. Nxh4 $5) 17... Ne7 $6 (17... h3 $1 18. Be3 hxg2 $11) 18. Nxh4 $16 Nf5 19. Bc1 (19. Bg5 $142 $1 Nxh4 20. Qxh4 $16) 19... Nxh4 20. Qxh4 { Classic example "c1>>c8". c4,d5,e6 are fixed on the 's c8 color. Hope for salvation is only } Qg6 21. Ba3 Re8 22. Ra2 Bd7 23. Bd6 Qf5 24. f4 Qh7 25. Qg5 Qf5 26. Qh4 Qh7 27. Qg5 Qf5 28. Qxf5 exf5 29. a5 Bc6 30. Rb2 Rad8 {} 31. Rfb1 $6 ({More chanses to win gave:} 31. g4 $142 $1 $18 {Only as ilustration:} g6 $140 32. Kg2 Kf7 33. Kg3 Rh8 34. Rbb1 fxg4 35. f5 $1 gxf5 36. Rxf5+ Kg6 37. Rf6+ Kg7 38. Kxg4 Rh2 39. Rg1 Bd7+ 40. Kf3+ Kh8 41. e6 $18) 31... Rd7 32. Bc5 a6 33. Kf2 Re6 34. Rh1 g6 35. Rbb1 Rh7 36. g4 Rxh1 37. Rxh1 fxg4 38. Kg3 Bd7 39. Kh4 Kg7 40. Bd6 Kf7 41. Kg3 Kg8 42. Rh4 Re8 1/2-1/2


