1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 g6 5. exd6 cxd6 6. c4 Nb6 7. Be2 Bg7 8. O-O O-O 9. Nc3 Nc6 10. b3 Bg4 11. Be3 d5 12. c5 Nc8 13. b4 a6 14. Rb1 e6 15. a4 N8e7 16. b5 axb5 17. axb5 Bxf3 18. Bxf3 Na5 19. Rb4 Nf5 20. Be2 Nxe3 {This move strengthens White's centre, but it is not easy to find a way to obtain effective counterplay.} (20... b6 $6 21. c6 (21. Na4 $5 bxc5 22. dxc5 Nxe3 23. fxe3 Qe7 24. Qd2 Rfb8 25. Rfb1 $14) 21... Qd6 22. Ra4 Rfd8 23. Qd2 $2 (23. Bd3 Nxe3 24. fxe3 f5 $14) 23... Nb3 24. Qa2 Rxa4 25. Nxa4 Nbxd4 26. Nxb6 Nxe3 27. fxe3 Nf5 $132 {Whitlock,H-Dive,R/NZL-ch63 corr 1996/Corr 2000 (1/2, 48)}) (20... Qh4 21. Qd2 (21. g3 $5 $14) 21... Nxe3 22. Qxe3 (22. fxe3 Be5 $1 {[%cal Gh4b4]} 23. g3 Bxg3 $1 $11) 22... Rfd8 (22... Nc4 23. Bxc4 Qxd4 24. Nxd5 exd5 25. Qxd4 Bxd4 26. Bxd5 Bxc5 27. Rc4 Rac8 $1 $11 {[%cal Gb7b6]} 28. Bxb7 $2 Bxf2+ $1 $17) 23. Rd1 e5 24. g3 exd4 25. Rbxd4 Bxd4 26. Rxd4 Qf6 27. Nxd5 $36 {Alozy,F-Odebrecht,A/corr 1995/Corr 2004 (1/2, 37)}) (20... Re8 {, as in the line with 20.d2, is less effective here, because of} 21. Bd3 {We can notice the difference. The d4-pawn is over proyected now and White can create the threat of xf5 at a convenient moment, thus releasing the pressure against d4 and discouraging ...e5.} Qe7 22. Ra4 $14) 21. fxe3 Qg5 22. Rf3 Rfd8 (22... e5 23. dxe5 Qxe5 24. Nxd5 Rfd8 25. Rd4 (25. e4 Nc6 $1 $132 {Badii,M (2255)-Fillon,D/Paris 1994/EXT 98 (1-0, 36)}) 25... f5 26. Rf2 $16 {Messing,H (2355)-Begovac,F (2405)/Pula 1993/EXT 99 (1-0, 31)}) (22... f5 23. Na4 f4 24. Nb6 Rad8 25. Ra4 (25. exf4 Rxf4 26. Qd2 Bh6 27. Qxf4 Qxf4 28. Rxf4 Bxf4 29. g3 Bc7 30. Na4 e5 31. Kf2 $14) 25... Nc4 26. Nxc4 dxc4 27. Bxc4 fxe3 28. Bxe6+ Kh8 $13 {Deschner,J-Joost,S/GER-ch qgA36 corr9395 1993/Corr Nr. 1 (1-0, 36)}) 23. Ra4 e5 24. e4 exd4 25. Nxd5 Nc6 $5 {An interesting, but insufficient sacrifice, offering only some practical chances in a difficult position.} (25... Bf8 26. Qc2 (26. Qxd4 $2 Nb3 $17) 26... Rdc8 27. Qa2 Bxc5 28. Bd3 b6 29. Nf6+ Kg7 30. Qxf7+ Kxf7 31. Nxh7+ $16) 26. Rxa8 Rxa8 27. bxc6 bxc6 28. Nb6 Ra7 29. Na4 Qe5 30. Bd3 Bh6 31. Qb3 Kg7 32. g3 Be3+ 33. Kg2 h5 34. h4 g5 35. hxg5 (35. Rf5 Qe6 36. Bc2 gxh4 37. Qxe6 fxe6 38. Rxh5 d3 39. Bb3 Rb7 40. Bxe6 d2 41. Bg4 Rb1 $14) 35... Qxg5 36. Bc2 Qg4 37. Bd1 (37. Qb2 $1 $18) 37... Qxe4 38. Bc2 Qe6 39. Qd3 Qg6 40. Qb3 Qg4 41. Qd3 Qg6 42. Qd1 Qe6 43. Kh2 Qa2 44. Qd3 Rxa4 45. Qh7+ Kf8 46. Qh8+ Ke7 47. Qe5+ Kf8 48. Kh3 Ra7 49. Qb8+ Kg7 50. Bb3 Qb1 51. Qe5+ f6 52. Qxf6+ Kh7 53. Bd1 Qg6 54. Rf5 Qxf6 55. Rxf6 Ra1 56. Bxh5 Rh1+ 57. Kg4 d3 58. Rf7+ Kg8 59. Rd7 d2 60. Bf7+ Kf8 61. Bb3 Rb1 62. Ba4 Bxc5 63. Kf5 Be3 64. Kg6 Ra1 65. Bxc6 1/2-1/2


