1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e6 3. e4 d5 4. e5 d4 5. exf6 dxc3 6. bxc3 Qxf6 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. d4 e5 9. Bg5 Qg6 10. d5 Nb8 11. Bd3 Bf5 12. Qa4+ Nd7 {At first in the post-mortem it seemed that 12...d7 might have been an error, but no clear refutation was found.} (12... c6 {was an interesting alternative.}) 13. O-O Bd6 14. Bxf5 Qxf5 15. c5 Bxc5 16. Nxe5 f6 17. g4 {Kortschnoj took a long time on this move, and the game now becomes wild. It is by no means clear that Ashley was in serious trouble, but precise defense was required and a few inaccurate moves led to defeat.} Qxe5 18. Rae1 O-O-O 19. Rxe5 Nxe5 20. Be3 Bxe3 21. fxe3 Kb8 {White has an advantage, but it is not easy to exploit.} 22. Qd4 h6 $2 ({Black needed to establish counterplay, and this could have been achieved with} 22... c6 23. c4 cxd5 24. cxd5 Rc8 $1) 23. c4 Rhe8 24. c5 c6 25. d6 Re6 26. Qe4 Ree8 27. Rb1 Ka8 28. Qh7 Rd7 29. Rb4 Rb8 30. Kg2 b5 31. Re4 a5 32. Qf5 Rbb7 33. Rxe5 fxe5 34. Qe4 Rd8 35. Qxc6 Kb8 36. Qa6 1-0


